## Laravel API Layer

### Routes

**Before (Blade routes):**

```php
// routes/web.php
Route::get('/products', [ProductController::class, 'index'])->name('products.index');
Route::post('/products', [ProductController::class, 'store']);
```

**After (API routes):**

```php
// routes/api.php
Route::post('/auth/login', [AuthController::class, 'login']);
Route::post('/auth/register', [AuthController::class, 'register']);

Route::middleware('auth:sanctum')->group(function () {
    Route::post('/auth/logout', [AuthController::class, 'logout']);
    Route::get('/auth/user', [AuthController::class, 'user']);
    Route::apiResource('products', ProductController::class);
});
```

---

### Controllers → Return JSON

**Before (Blade/Inertia controller):**

```php
public function index()
{
    return Inertia::render('Products/Index', ['products' => Product::all()]);
}
```

**After (API controller):**

```php
use App\Http\Resources\ProductResource;

public function index(): \Illuminate\Http\Resources\Json\AnonymousResourceCollection
{
    return ProductResource::collection(Product::paginate(20));
}

public function show(Product $product): ProductResource
{
    return new ProductResource($product);
}

public function store(Request $request): ProductResource
{
    $data = $request->validate([
        'name'  => 'required|string|max:255',
        'price' => 'required|numeric|min:0',
    ]);
    return new ProductResource(Product::create($data));
}

public function update(Request $request, Product $product): ProductResource
{
    $product->update($request->validate(['name' => 'string', 'price' => 'numeric']));
    return new ProductResource($product);
}

public function destroy(Product $product): \Illuminate\Http\JsonResponse
{
    $product->delete();
    return response()->json(['message' => 'Deleted.']);
}
```

