## Migration Checklist

### Laravel API Setup
- [ ] Convert all Blade/Inertia controllers to return `JsonResource`
- [ ] Add `apiResource` routes to `routes/api.php`
- [ ] Remove `routes/web.php` page routes (or replace with a single catch-all for the SPA)
- [ ] Install and configure Laravel Sanctum
- [ ] Add `HasApiTokens` trait to `User` model
- [ ] Create API resources for all models exposed to the frontend
- [ ] Configure `config/cors.php` with the React dev server origin
- [ ] Test all API endpoints with Postman/Insomnia

### React SPA Setup
- [ ] Create React app: `npm create vite@latest my-app -- --template react-ts`
- [ ] Install React Router: `npm install react-router-dom`
- [ ] Install Axios: `npm install axios`
- [ ] Create `src/api/client.ts` with base URL, auth header, and 401 interceptor
- [ ] Add `VITE_API_URL` to `.env`
- [ ] Set up `src/router.tsx` with all page routes
- [ ] Map each Laravel web route to a React Router route
- [ ] Replace each Blade page with a React page component
- [ ] Replace Livewire `mount()` data loads with `useEffect + client.get()`
- [ ] Replace Livewire form actions with `client.post/put/delete()`
- [ ] Handle 422 validation errors in each form
- [ ] Add auth login/logout flow with token storage
- [ ] Add `ProtectedRoute` wrapper for authenticated pages
- [ ] Test CORS — no errors in browser network tab

